<p>So... What exactly is HTML? HTML is a markup programming language. <pre>A programming language is like english, kind of. It is the language computers understand. They read each line, so you can tell the computer <br> <code>clean the dishes <br> make my bed</code><br> And the computer will clean the dishes, when it is done, it will make your bed. The computers understand different programming languages, like you understand different languages! Computer languages, another way of calling them, look somehow like this:<br><code>clean_the_dishes();<br>make_my_bed();<br></code>, but then, how is HTML a programming language? HTML is a <strong>markup language</strong>. It's <strong><a href="#syntax">syntax</a></strong> is different.</pre></p>

