<div id="firstwebsite"><h1>Your first website!</h1>
<p>So... Let's start coding! To make a website, you just need a text editor! Any text editor would work, I recommend Sublime Text 3, and it is the editor I am using for this tutorial. If you use windows then open Notepad, not Word because Word is a RTF (Rich Text Format) editor and we need a TXT (Plain Text) editor. In mac, open TextEdit, and in Ubuntu Linux, use gedit. If you use other Linux distrobutions, just use your default text editor.</p>
<p>Now, in your text editor, create a file and call it index.html <br> Then, in the part where you write, copy this text and paste it in the editor: <br><code>&lt;h1&gt;Hi world!&lt;/h1&gt;</code><br>Then, search for the file. In mac, open finder, in windows open the file explorer. In ubuntu linux open nautilus or your default file browser. double click the file. if you opened it right you should have something like this: <br><pre><div class="browser"><h1>Hi World!</h1></div></pre>Congratulations! You made your first website! Now, try adding <br><code>&lt;h2&gt;Small text&lt;/h2&gt;</code><br>And refresh the page: See the smaller text? It is because you added an <code>&lt;h2&gt;</code>!The H2 tag is smaller than the H1 tag! The tags define what the content would look like, and act like. The different tags you need to know right now are: <table><tr><th>Tag</th></tr><tr><td><h1>H1</h1></td></tr><tr><td><h2>H2</h2></td></tr><tr><td><h3>H3</h3></td></tr><tr><td><h4>H4</h4></td></tr><tr><td><h5>H5</h5></td></tr><tr><td><h6>H6</h6></td></tr></table><br>
So, the tags go in <strong>lowercase</strong>, and, inside the tags!</p>
